  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Prime Minister tells how to distribute gas",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe said in the Parliament today that since 33 thousand metric tons of gas is to be received from June 11 to the first week of August, the current shortage of gas will disappear by the end of June or the first week of August.",
        "The Prime Minister also said that from July 11 or 12, 112,000 gas cylinders will be continuously distributed daily throughout the island.",
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe also said that it is planned to distribute gas at 140 locations in Colombo on July 11 and 12, and 140,000 cylinders of 100 kilograms of 12 kg each will be distributed within two days.",
        "The Prime Minister said that 25,000 cylinders of 12 kg each, which is the daily requirement of Colombo city, will be released, and the release of gas for bakeries and small-scale businesses will also be done simultaneously, the Prime Minister said.",
        "The Prime Minister said that all these matters may be subject to changes depending on the weather and the nature of the sea, but he is confident that he can provide gas for the next 4 months without shortage."
      ],
